.TH "PVXCHAIN" "1" "2026-03-01" "pvx" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
pvxchain \- Managed serial chain runner
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B pvxchain
.SH DESCRIPTION
Auto-generated from built-in --help output.
.SH OPTIONS
.nf
usage: pvx chain [\-h] \-\-pipeline PIPELINE \-\-output OUTPUT
                 [\-\-work\-dir WORK_DIR] [\-\-keep\-intermediate] [\-\-example]
                 input

Managed one\-line chain runner for serial pvx audio tools. Each stage receives
the previous stage output as input.

positional arguments:
  input                 Initial input audio path or '\-' for stdin

options:
  \-h, \-\-help            show this help message and exit
  \-\-pipeline PIPELINE   Pipeline string with stages separated by '|'. Example:
                        "voc \-\-stretch 1.2 | formant \-\-mode preserve"
  \-\-output, \-\-out OUTPUT
                        Final output path (or '\-')
  \-\-work\-dir WORK_DIR   Optional directory for intermediate stage files
  \-\-keep\-intermediate   Keep intermediate stage files after successful
                        completion
  \-\-example             Print a copy\-paste chain example and exit
.fi
